		tr
			td(colspan="2")
				h3 OneNote for iOS 2.0
				h5 <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/microsoft-onenote-for-iphone/id410395246">iPhone</a> | <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/microsoft-onenote-for-ipad/id478105721">iPad</a>
		tr.poweritem
			td.poweritem-icon
				i.icon-edit.icon-2x
			td.poweritem
				| <a href="http://onenote.com">OneNote</a> is a beautiful notetaking app and part of the
				| <a href="http://office.com">Office</a> suite. OneNote helps you keep track of things in life and runs on desktops, laptops, tablets, phones
				| and browsers. It keeps your notes in sync across all devices.
		tr.poweritem
			td.poweritem-icon
				i.icon-thumbs-up.icon-2x
			td.poweritem
				| My team was responsible for the overhaul of OneNote 2.0 for iOS. We created a full-blown OneNote
				| version for iOS with a completely redesigned user interface. For more details, check out 
				| <a href="http://thenextweb.com/microsoft/2013/07/01/onenote-for-android-and-ios-updated-with-consistent-formatting-office-365-syncing-unlimited-notes-and-more/">The Next Web</a>,
				| <a href="http://www.theverge.com/2013/7/1/4482868/onenote-android-iphone-ipad-version-2-update-features">The Verge</a>
				| and <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/07/01/onenote/">Engadget</a>. This update
				| helped our iPad app improve its App Store rating from 3 to 4 stars.
		tr.poweritem
			td.poweritem-icon
				i.icon-dashboard.icon-2x
			td.poweritem
				| Rearchitected the app to be asynchronous and multithreaded using <a href="http://developer.apple.com/library/ios/#documentation/Performance/Reference/GCD_libdispatch_Ref/Reference/reference.html">
				| Grand Central Dispatch</a>, making the app 74% more responsive.
		tr.poweritem
			td.poweritem-icon
				i.icon-th-list.icon-2x
			td.poweritem
