			td(colspan="2")
				h3 Mayorita
		tr.poweritem
			td.poweritem-icon
				img(src="/images/mayorino.png")
			td.poweritem
				| <a href="http://mayorita.com">Mayorita</a> is a free web service that lets users tap into the
				| knowledge and opinions of others by asking any yes/no question and getting
				| an aggregated answer within seconds! Mayorita is the easiest, fastest and most reliable
				| way to leverage the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wisdom_of_the_crowd">wisdom
				| of the crowd</a>.
				| Mayorita is available on <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.mayorita.android">Android</a>,
				| <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/mayorita/id668406560">iOS</a> and the web. Try a hassle-free demo on <a href="https://www.mayorita.com">mayorita.com</a>.
		tr.poweritem
			td.poweritem-icon
				i.icon-mobile-phone.icon-3x
			td.poweritem
				| Designed and implemented Mayorita for iOS in Objective C, Cocoa Touch and
				| <a href="http://developer.apple.com/library/ios/#documentation/DataManagement/Conceptual/iPhoneCoreData01/Introduction/Introduction.html">
				| Core Data</a>. Used the following open source libraries: 
				| <a href="http://afnetworking.com">AFNetworking</a>,
				| <a href="https://github.com/jdg/MBProgressHUD">MBProgressHUD</a>,
				| <a href="https://github.com/romaonthego/REComposeViewController">REComposeViewController</a> 
				| (check out the screenshots below).
		tr.poweritem
			td.poweritem-icon
				i.icon-rocket.icon-2x
			td.poweritem
				| Led the development of the backend server in <a href="http://rubyonrails.org">Ruby on Rails</a>,
				| defined features and helped integrate the backend with its mobile applications.
